Normalized scores, which ranged from 0 to 100, were used for reliability assessment through Cronbach’s alpha and omega (Dunn et al. 2014) within each factor (Revelle 2017). Scores were normalized for each item, then each metric (systems, staff, supplies, and space), and then the overall surge score, using a standard formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$X_{normalized} = \left( {x - x_{min} } \right){/}\left( {x_{max} - m_{min} } \right)$$\end{document}Xnormalized=x-xmin/xmax-mminSince no maximum upper values exist for numeric variables, we normalized the score for the maximum value of each variable to the year 2014 (“Appendix”, Surge Index Function).
